    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty strong stance. You mentioned that data shows it can help low-income drivers, but I've been reading a lot of pushback about it basically being a regressive tax that punishes people who have to commute from outside the city center. How do you reconcile that criticism with the benefits you listed?",
